communications.subject: Washington Public Records Act Request: Brady List (March 2025) (Okanogan County Prosecuting Attorney)
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Washington Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

All current "Brady lists" and "Giglio lists" (per Brady v. Maryland/Giglio v. United States) maintained by your office.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Rose Terse

communications.subject: Your Okanogan County, Washington public records request #25-337 has been closed.
communications.communication:
Okanogan County, Washington ************************************************************************ Record request #25-337 has been closed. The closure reason supplied was: Hello Rose Terse, We believe that your request is fulfilled because copies of all responsive records have been provided and it is closed as of this date. The PRA allows for a one-year statute of limitations to seek judicial review, and that time starts as of the date of this email/letter. We do not intend to disclose further records or further address this request unless you submit additional questions within two weeks from this date. If you believe our response is incomplete, we have misunderstood your request, or you have questions, please contact me immediately. We can discuss any errors or omissions you believe were made in our response. We are confident we can address any concerns you may have. Thank you ************************************************************************ Questions about your request? Reply to this email or sign in to contact staff at Okanogan County, Washington.
